    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/1291</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-10">December 10,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chinese Ambassador called this evening to see me at his request.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador left with me the texts of his Government’s declarations of war
                    upon Japan and upon Germany and Italy. These are attached herewith.<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d566fn32">Dated December 9; for texts, see Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>. December 13, 1941, p. 506.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Ambassador also left with me a personal message addressed by the
                    Generalissimo to the President.<note n="33" xml:id="d566fn33">See <hi
                            rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 508.</note> I told the Ambassador I would
                    transmit this at once to the President, who I knew would be very deeply moved by
                    this message. A copy of this message is likewise attached herewith.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
